WEBVTT

00:00:00.600 --> 00:00:02.300
[CHOKES] Jade? It's Kiko!

00:00:02.300 --> 00:00:04.500
- Kiko?
- Kiko from Hotel 88.

00:00:04.500 --> 00:00:06.067
You haven't been
coming home anymore.

00:00:06.067 --> 00:00:07.100
Why is that?

00:00:07.100 --> 00:00:07.967
Because you're toxic.

00:00:07.967 --> 00:00:11.633
You're an
irresponsible drunk.

00:00:11.633 --> 00:00:13.433
That's why I asked you
to come here, kids.

00:00:13.433 --> 00:00:15.100
So we can fix this.

00:00:15.100 --> 00:00:17.067
Even this hotel.

00:00:17.067 --> 00:00:18.267
Let's restore it.

00:00:18.267 --> 00:00:19.433
What happened?!

00:00:19.433 --> 00:00:21.333
[PEOPLE CLAMORING]

00:00:21.333 --> 00:00:23.067
Pa!

00:00:23.067 --> 00:00:26.400
Dad! [SOBS]

00:00:26.400 --> 00:00:27.233
Dad!

00:00:27.233 --> 00:00:29.233
- Fred!
- You can't come near.

00:00:29.233 --> 00:00:30.133
[SOBBING]

00:00:30.133 --> 00:00:32.433
This shouldn't have
happened to Dad.

00:00:33.100 --> 00:00:34.567
We won't stop...

00:00:35.367 --> 00:00:37.567
until someone pays for
what happened to Dad.

00:00:38.267 --> 00:00:41.300
[SOBBING]

00:00:41.300 --> 00:00:43.467
Are you going to the morgue?

00:00:43.467 --> 00:00:44.600
No.

00:00:44.600 --> 00:00:46.133
What's the point?
The police are already there.

00:00:46.133 --> 00:00:47.400
Papa is dead!

00:00:49.633 --> 00:00:51.033
I know.

00:00:51.033 --> 00:00:52.500
So what am I supposed to do?

00:00:52.500 --> 00:00:54.333
Go visit him.
Show that you care!

00:00:56.367 --> 00:00:57.333
Why?

00:00:58.633 --> 00:01:00.167
Will it make a difference?

00:01:00.667 --> 00:01:01.667
[HUFFS] Wow.

00:01:02.700 --> 00:01:04.667
You guys are unbelievable!

00:01:04.667 --> 00:01:07.467
What? You can't even
show a little concern?

00:01:07.500 --> 00:01:09.667
[GIO] The last time I saw Papa,
I was just a kid.

00:01:10.467 --> 00:01:11.167
When my mother died

00:01:11.167 --> 00:01:12.667
we lost contact after that.

00:01:13.800 --> 00:01:15.467
So there's no reason
for me to stay

00:01:15.467 --> 00:01:16.633
now that he's gone.

00:01:16.633 --> 00:01:20.500
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

00:01:20.500 --> 00:01:22.200
What, are you leaving too?

00:01:23.067 --> 00:01:30.067
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:01:30.067 --> 00:01:31.300
[SIGHS]

00:01:31.300 --> 00:01:38.267
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

00:02:32.567 --> 00:02:34.767
Oh, why are you back already?

00:02:34.767 --> 00:02:36.267
You should've told me
you were coming home.

00:02:36.267 --> 00:02:38.333
I haven't cooked yet.

00:02:39.267 --> 00:02:40.600
What happened?

00:02:40.600 --> 00:02:41.600
How did it go?

00:02:44.533 --> 00:02:46.267
Papa's gone.

00:02:47.400 --> 00:02:48.533
What?

00:02:50.133 --> 00:02:51.933
He was found dead.

00:02:51.933 --> 00:02:53.400
They still don't know why.

00:02:54.633 --> 00:02:55.633
Uh, but...

00:02:55.633 --> 00:02:59.400
W-Why are you here?
Shouldn't you be there?

00:03:01.167 --> 00:03:08.100
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

00:03:11.933 --> 00:03:13.133
[SLAMS TABLE]

00:03:14.833 --> 00:03:21.767
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:03:26.600 --> 00:03:28.433
[YOUNG GIO] Grandma?

00:03:29.600 --> 00:03:31.733
Did Papa not come?

00:03:33.167 --> 00:03:35.500
Did he not come
to Mama's funeral?

00:03:36.333 --> 00:03:37.567
No, sweetie.

00:03:38.433 --> 00:03:41.700
No one saw him at the church...

00:03:41.700 --> 00:03:44.200
or at the cemetery.

00:03:44.200 --> 00:03:45.767
How could Papa do this?

00:03:46.500 --> 00:03:49.800
Mama is already gone,
and he still didn't come!

00:03:49.800 --> 00:03:53.633
[SOBBING]

00:03:53.633 --> 00:03:55.800
Grandma's here, sweetie.

00:03:55.833 --> 00:03:57.700
I'm not going to leave you.

00:03:58.833 --> 00:04:01.333
I promise, I won't leave you.

00:04:02.700 --> 00:04:04.467
[SNIFFLING, WHIMPERING]

00:04:06.333 --> 00:04:07.767
Papa is a bad person.

00:04:08.800 --> 00:04:10.367
I don't want him anymore.

00:04:11.000 --> 00:04:12.867
I don't want him anymore!

00:04:12.867 --> 00:04:15.233
I don't want him anymore!

00:04:15.233 --> 00:04:16.867
I don't have
any parents anymore!

00:04:17.667 --> 00:04:19.333
[YOUNG GIO SOBBING]

00:04:19.333 --> 00:04:22.233
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:04:22.233 --> 00:04:25.167
[SNIFFLES]

00:04:38.667 --> 00:04:45.633
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

00:04:45.900 --> 00:04:47.633
Sir.

00:04:50.700 --> 00:04:57.667
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:05:11.967 --> 00:05:16.400
[LINE RINGING]

00:05:16.400 --> 00:05:17.400
Pa.

00:05:18.300 --> 00:05:19.933
What did you do to my office?

00:05:20.933 --> 00:05:23.933
I sold the bookstore
to GS Malls.

00:05:27.067 --> 00:05:29.900
You didn't even tell me
before you did that?

00:05:29.900 --> 00:05:32.533
[CARLOS] It's a
business decision, Martin.

00:05:33.267 --> 00:05:34.700
Nothing personal.

00:05:42.933 --> 00:05:46.833
[MUSIC TURNS MOROSE]

00:05:46.833 --> 00:05:48.567
[MIKE] What exactly happened?

00:05:49.467 --> 00:05:51.067
[YOUNG MARTIN] I don't want to
go home anymore.

00:05:52.467 --> 00:05:54.733
Why? Are you having
problems with your mom?

00:05:55.600 --> 00:05:58.467
Her husband.
He hates me, Papa.

00:05:59.067 --> 00:06:00.567
He doesn't like me.

00:06:01.600 --> 00:06:03.967
Can I just stay here with you,
Papa?

00:06:06.767 --> 00:06:10.300
You need to understand, son.

00:06:10.333 --> 00:06:13.100
You need to go back
to your mom's family.

00:06:13.100 --> 00:06:14.500
It's time to go back to them.

00:06:15.800 --> 00:06:17.767
Do you not want me
anymore either, Papa?

00:06:18.600 --> 00:06:20.533
It's not like that.

00:06:20.533 --> 00:06:22.067
It is like that, Papa!

00:06:23.867 --> 00:06:27.733
You'd rather drink
than be a father to me!

00:06:28.433 --> 00:06:29.300
No...

00:06:30.633 --> 00:06:31.633
Martin!

00:06:32.333 --> 00:06:33.433
Martin, son.

00:06:38.133 --> 00:06:43.867
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:06:43.900 --> 00:06:50.833
[CRYING, SNIFFLING]

00:07:02.000 --> 00:07:03.133
[CLEARS THROAT]

00:07:03.133 --> 00:07:05.167
Um, hon?

00:07:05.167 --> 00:07:06.533
You want something?

00:07:06.533 --> 00:07:07.900
Oh, no.

00:07:07.900 --> 00:07:09.500
[TRIXIE] Hello, Mom, Dad!

00:07:09.500 --> 00:07:12.033
I am so sorry I am late.

00:07:12.033 --> 00:07:13.833
Oh! Hello, big brother.

00:07:13.833 --> 00:07:15.833
I haven't seen you for days.

00:07:15.867 --> 00:07:17.567
Hi.

00:07:17.567 --> 00:07:20.767
Martin, you remember
Mr. Dy, right?

00:07:20.767 --> 00:07:21.833
I was in a meeting with him
earlier,

00:07:21.833 --> 00:07:26.067
and he finally agreed
to sell me the property.

00:07:26.067 --> 00:07:28.700
We can now start
on the new project.

00:07:28.700 --> 00:07:29.767
[LOUISE] Ah, that's nice.

00:07:29.767 --> 00:07:31.900
[CARLOS]
That's great news, Trixie.

00:07:31.900 --> 00:07:33.133
You know what?

00:07:33.700 --> 00:07:36.533
You really take after me
when it comes to charm.

00:07:36.533 --> 00:07:37.400
[TRIXIE CHUCKLES]

00:07:37.400 --> 00:07:38.533
You got it, Dad.

00:07:39.600 --> 00:07:41.700
And how about you, Martin?

00:07:41.700 --> 00:07:42.667
How are you?

00:07:43.167 --> 00:07:44.067
I don't know.

00:07:45.867 --> 00:07:47.100
Why?

00:07:47.100 --> 00:07:48.400
What's wrong?

00:07:49.133 --> 00:07:50.433
I don't know either.

00:07:51.933 --> 00:07:53.567
First,

00:07:53.867 --> 00:07:56.467
I didn't know I wouldn't even
have an office to return to

00:07:56.467 --> 00:07:58.767
after coming back
from Solara Island.

00:07:58.767 --> 00:08:00.133
[LOUISE] Solara Island?

00:08:00.133 --> 00:08:06.733
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

00:08:06.733 --> 00:08:08.567
[MARTIN] Don't worry.

00:08:08.567 --> 00:08:10.900
I'm not going back there
anymore.

00:08:10.900 --> 00:08:12.567
Huh?

00:08:12.567 --> 00:08:14.733
But didn't you just
reconnect with your dad?

00:08:14.733 --> 00:08:16.600
Because he's dead.

00:08:16.600 --> 00:08:17.733
[LOUISE] Huh?

00:08:20.633 --> 00:08:22.567
Son, what happened?

00:08:22.600 --> 00:08:24.100
- Excuse me.
- [CHAIR SCRAPES]

00:08:24.900 --> 00:08:25.900
Martin.

00:08:25.900 --> 00:08:32.767
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

00:08:34.767 --> 00:08:36.800
We keep delivering
vegetables to you

00:08:36.800 --> 00:08:38.967
and you don't even know
how to pay?!

00:08:38.967 --> 00:08:40.733
I promise to pay you
next time!

00:08:40.733 --> 00:08:42.933
- I promise.
- I don't need your promises!

00:08:42.933 --> 00:08:45.067
The first time you did that,
fine.

00:08:45.067 --> 00:08:46.667
The second time,
I tried to understand.

00:08:46.667 --> 00:08:48.133
But the third time?
Still the same thing?

00:08:48.133 --> 00:08:49.600
Now you're just taking
advantage of my kindness!

00:08:49.600 --> 00:08:51.567
- I'm sorry. I will pay.
- Too late!

00:08:51.567 --> 00:08:53.733
No! Cheska, take that.
Hurry up!

00:08:53.733 --> 00:08:56.267
- I have had enough already.
- Sorry...

00:08:56.300 --> 00:08:57.867
Sorry.

00:08:57.867 --> 00:08:58.967
Come on, come on.

00:08:58.967 --> 00:09:00.633
This is ridiculous!

00:09:00.633 --> 00:09:02.500
She's not the only one
with bills to pay!

00:09:02.500 --> 00:09:04.133
- Yeah.
- Unbelievable.

00:09:04.967 --> 00:09:06.633
- Geez.
- Ma!

00:09:06.633 --> 00:09:08.067
- Oh.
- Kiko!

00:09:09.767 --> 00:09:11.133
What are you doing here?

00:09:11.133 --> 00:09:12.933
I saw the multicab parked.

00:09:12.933 --> 00:09:14.167
So I got down here.

00:09:15.300 --> 00:09:17.633
Why did you come home
all of a sudden?

00:09:17.633 --> 00:09:19.267
Yeah.

00:09:19.267 --> 00:09:20.267
Are you okay?

00:09:21.500 --> 00:09:23.700
[GEORGIA SOBS]

00:09:23.700 --> 00:09:30.633
[SOBBING CONTINUES]

00:09:31.633 --> 00:09:32.800
Ma.

00:09:32.800 --> 00:09:33.800
Ma!

00:09:34.700 --> 00:09:38.000
- Ma, I thought...
- [WAILS]

00:09:38.000 --> 00:09:40.867
Shouldn't Kiko
be the one crying?

00:09:40.867 --> 00:09:43.067
What's it to you?!

00:09:43.067 --> 00:09:46.300
Michael was a jerk,
but I loved him!

00:09:46.900 --> 00:09:48.033
[ENGINE STARTS]

00:09:49.200 --> 00:09:52.533
[GEORGIA WAILS]

00:09:56.633 --> 00:09:58.000
- [CERAMIC BREAKS]
- [KIKO] Ma?

00:09:58.000 --> 00:09:59.500
I might stay there for a while.

00:10:00.200 --> 00:10:03.800
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

00:10:03.833 --> 00:10:07.700
Ma, wasn't this supposed to be
for your dream phone?

00:10:08.333 --> 00:10:10.167
It's okay.

00:10:10.167 --> 00:10:13.000
This still isn't enough
to make up for everything.

00:10:13.000 --> 00:10:16.700
Ma, I don't hold
anything against you.

00:10:16.700 --> 00:10:19.233
Yes, because
you're a good son.

00:10:19.233 --> 00:10:23.333
If I told you to
go there and demand money,

00:10:23.333 --> 00:10:24.667
you would.

00:10:24.667 --> 00:10:26.833
If I told you to stay here

00:10:26.833 --> 00:10:30.633
so we could save money,
you would too.

00:10:32.167 --> 00:10:34.667
Ma, this my choice.

00:10:34.700 --> 00:10:38.900
Maybe I just use
being busy as an excuse...

00:10:38.900 --> 00:10:40.600
because it's lonely now, right?

00:10:41.933 --> 00:10:44.000
The hotel has really changed.

00:10:48.200 --> 00:10:50.233
What if...

00:10:50.233 --> 00:10:52.200
Michael and I
ended up together?

00:10:53.233 --> 00:10:55.033
Then Cheska wouldn't exist.

00:10:56.733 --> 00:10:57.600
He's right.

00:10:57.600 --> 00:11:00.133
No one would inherit
your beauty, Ma.

00:11:00.133 --> 00:11:01.100
[KIKO CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

00:11:01.100 --> 00:11:02.700
That's true too.

00:11:03.900 --> 00:11:06.067
It's just that
sometimes I think...

00:11:06.067 --> 00:11:09.067
maybe things wouldn't have
been so complicated if...

00:11:09.100 --> 00:11:10.767
Michael and I
worked things out.

00:11:11.400 --> 00:11:14.067
But your father and I...

00:11:15.233 --> 00:11:16.967
we were never really
compatible.

00:11:18.667 --> 00:11:25.633
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:11:25.633 --> 00:11:27.233
But I love you.

00:11:29.133 --> 00:11:33.100
And Michael,
may his soul rest in peace.

00:11:33.100 --> 00:11:34.733
He loved you.

00:11:34.733 --> 00:11:36.333
I know he did.

00:11:36.333 --> 00:11:41.100
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:11:41.100 --> 00:11:42.367
Alright.

00:11:46.333 --> 00:11:48.667
Sir Michael was kind.

00:11:48.667 --> 00:11:50.000
He was a jolly person.

00:11:50.000 --> 00:11:52.033
He was a father to us.

00:11:52.033 --> 00:11:53.300
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

00:11:53.300 --> 00:11:55.367
Uh, that afternoon,

00:11:55.367 --> 00:11:57.033
I saw him leave.

00:11:57.033 --> 00:11:58.467
He was in a hurry.

00:11:58.467 --> 00:12:00.333
But that was it.

00:12:08.967 --> 00:12:10.700
Did you see him talking
to someone

00:12:10.700 --> 00:12:12.567
who may have led him
to be in that disposition?

00:12:14.900 --> 00:12:17.333
He was holding a phone.

00:12:17.333 --> 00:12:19.533
But I didn't know
who he was talking to.

00:12:23.733 --> 00:12:26.833
I saw a car coming,

00:12:26.833 --> 00:12:29.800
and two men got out of it.

00:12:29.800 --> 00:12:30.933
And then?

00:12:31.567 --> 00:12:34.033
I think they seem
to have gotten physical.

00:12:34.033 --> 00:12:35.933
Things got pretty heated.

00:12:40.900 --> 00:12:43.367
After that,
I just ignored them.

00:12:43.367 --> 00:12:44.700
I went inside my house.

00:12:45.733 --> 00:12:47.767
Then I heard gunshots.

00:12:50.367 --> 00:12:53.300
By the time I got out,
both of them were dead.

00:12:57.600 --> 00:12:59.767
Is no one else living
around here?

00:12:59.767 --> 00:13:06.800
[FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:13:09.900 --> 00:13:15.433
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

00:13:15.433 --> 00:13:16.400
Son,

00:13:17.433 --> 00:13:18.667
it's okay to cry, alright?

00:13:21.400 --> 00:13:22.567
I already did, Ma.

00:13:24.533 --> 00:13:25.533
Kiko...

00:13:26.567 --> 00:13:28.433
you can cry again
if you need to.

00:13:29.900 --> 00:13:31.600
Especially if you feel like it.

00:13:37.533 --> 00:13:38.533
Oh!

00:13:39.433 --> 00:13:40.800
Group hug! Group hug!

00:13:40.800 --> 00:13:44.067
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:13:44.067 --> 00:13:50.033
- [FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]
- [WIND GUSHING]

00:13:50.033 --> 00:13:52.133
- Kiko? Kiko!
- [PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

00:13:52.133 --> 00:13:54.467
Raphie... what is it?

00:13:54.500 --> 00:13:55.933
Kiko, the cops are here.

00:14:04.167 --> 00:14:07.000
[WIND CHIMES CLINKING]

00:14:07.000 --> 00:14:08.767
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

00:14:11.000 --> 00:14:13.633
U-Uncle Federico killed Papa?

00:14:15.567 --> 00:14:17.167
The investigation
progressed quickly

00:14:17.167 --> 00:14:19.733
because of the strong testimony
of the witness.

00:14:19.733 --> 00:14:23.467
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:14:23.467 --> 00:14:26.800
A witness saw
Mr. Fernandez's car arriving,

00:14:26.800 --> 00:14:28.667
and he was with Mr. Almazan.

00:14:28.700 --> 00:14:31.000
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

00:14:31.000 --> 00:14:33.800
No one knows what
they could've fought about.

00:14:34.867 --> 00:14:37.933
- [BOTH GRUNTING] Argh!
- [GUNSHOTS]

00:14:39.000 --> 00:14:40.700
[GUNSHOT]

00:14:40.700 --> 00:14:42.067
[GUN COCKS, GUNSHOT]

00:14:43.433 --> 00:14:45.800
[HENRI] The bullets found
on the victims' bodies

00:14:45.800 --> 00:14:48.000
were from
a murder weapon.

00:14:48.000 --> 00:14:50.500
And the murder weapon
found at the crime scene

00:14:50.500 --> 00:14:53.767
was registered to
Mr. Michael Fernandez.

00:14:53.767 --> 00:14:55.967
Both of their fingerprints
were on the gun.

00:14:56.867 --> 00:14:59.467
Both had gunpowder residue
on their hands.

00:15:00.600 --> 00:15:02.667
Proof that both of them
fired the gun.

00:15:02.700 --> 00:15:06.900
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:15:06.900 --> 00:15:09.967
Mr. Michael Fernandez and
Mr. Federico Almazan

00:15:09.967 --> 00:15:11.200
killed each other.

00:15:12.000 --> 00:15:13.500
N- No. [BREATHING HEAVILY]

00:15:13.500 --> 00:15:15.500
No! That's not true!

00:15:15.500 --> 00:15:18.167
My Daddy isn't a murderer!

00:15:18.167 --> 00:15:20.967
- That was self-defense!
- [GLUM MUSIC PLAYING]

00:15:20.967 --> 00:15:22.867
- Leon... Leon...
- Sir.

00:15:24.167 --> 00:15:25.333
What would happen to the case

00:15:25.333 --> 00:15:27.667
if it's true
that they killed each other?

00:15:28.800 --> 00:15:31.033
We no longer have
leading suspects to be charged.

00:15:31.867 --> 00:15:33.000
This is now a case closed.

00:15:34.200 --> 00:15:35.633
[JADE SOBBING] No...

00:15:39.200 --> 00:15:40.200
That's it?

00:15:42.767 --> 00:15:44.200
My Dad was killed then--

00:15:45.100 --> 00:15:46.233
That's unfair!

00:15:49.233 --> 00:15:50.733
[JADE SNIFFLES]

00:15:53.100 --> 00:15:54.533
We'll get going.

00:15:54.533 --> 00:16:00.067
[JADE SOBBING]

00:16:00.067 --> 00:16:05.233
[GLUM MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:16:11.800 --> 00:16:14.233
We've already cleared out
some of the clutter here

00:16:14.233 --> 00:16:16.567
in your dad's library.

00:16:19.700 --> 00:16:21.700
If you need anything
from his belongings,

00:16:21.700 --> 00:16:23.433
it's all here.

00:16:34.567 --> 00:16:36.200
Monette,
everything has to be in order

00:16:36.200 --> 00:16:38.267
so Papa can have
a proper funeral.

00:16:43.400 --> 00:16:46.733
Did Papa ever say
what he wanted when he dies?

00:16:47.733 --> 00:16:48.833
[SIGHS]

00:16:48.833 --> 00:16:51.233
No, but...

00:16:51.233 --> 00:16:53.367
...I wish your brothers
were here.

00:16:56.167 --> 00:16:58.367
[SCOFFS] Let's not get
our hopes up about that.

00:17:00.633 --> 00:17:02.233
Still, let them know.

00:17:04.233 --> 00:17:07.500
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

00:17:07.500 --> 00:17:09.600
Alright, I'll leave you here
for now.

00:17:09.600 --> 00:17:12.567
If you need anything,
just call me.

00:17:12.567 --> 00:17:14.133
- Okay?
- Alright.

00:17:15.700 --> 00:17:21.667
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:17:27.767 --> 00:17:34.600
[LINE RINGING]

00:17:34.600 --> 00:17:35.633
[BEEPS]

00:17:39.433 --> 00:17:44.200
[LINE RINGING]

00:17:44.200 --> 00:17:45.233
[BEEPS]

00:17:45.600 --> 00:17:48.500
[KEYPAD CLICKING]

00:17:48.533 --> 00:17:55.500
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:18:00.533 --> 00:18:01.633
[PHONE DINGS]

00:18:02.567 --> 00:18:05.800
[KIKO] Papa's autopsy
results are out.

00:18:05.800 --> 00:18:08.600
You might want to see him
before he's buried.

00:18:13.333 --> 00:18:15.167
Grandma, I'm heading out!

00:18:15.167 --> 00:18:17.400
I still have a viewing
with my client.

00:18:17.400 --> 00:18:19.933
Oh, okay, sweetheart.
Be careful, alright?

00:18:20.633 --> 00:18:23.867
I'll cook dinner later
when you get home.

00:18:24.833 --> 00:18:26.533
Okay, Grandma.
I'm heading out.

00:18:26.533 --> 00:18:28.233
- Okay, okay.
- [SMOOCHES]

00:18:28.233 --> 00:18:29.600
- Take care, alright?
- Bye.

00:18:29.600 --> 00:18:30.933
- Be careful!
- Yes!

00:18:30.933 --> 00:18:32.667
"Papa's autopsy results
are out.

00:18:32.667 --> 00:18:34.733
You might want to see him
before he's buried."

00:18:37.833 --> 00:18:39.833
Oh, you're not going to work?

00:18:39.833 --> 00:18:41.833
After they shut down
my business?

00:18:42.667 --> 00:18:43.833
[TRIXIE SIGHS]

00:18:43.833 --> 00:18:45.500
Martin, don't worry about it.

00:18:45.500 --> 00:18:48.567
I'm sure you'll find
something new to keep you busy.

00:18:48.567 --> 00:18:49.667
I should.

00:18:49.667 --> 00:18:51.000
I don't want to just
do nothing.

00:18:51.000 --> 00:18:52.500
You? Doing nothing?

00:18:52.500 --> 00:18:54.200
You're even more of a
workaholic than Dad.

00:18:55.433 --> 00:18:58.700
Here, just a suggestion.

00:18:58.700 --> 00:19:00.633
What if you take a break
for now?

00:19:00.633 --> 00:19:02.367
That's different from
doing nothing.

00:19:02.367 --> 00:19:03.567
Nope.

00:19:03.567 --> 00:19:05.233
Why would I take a break?

00:19:07.367 --> 00:19:09.200
You're really something,
you know that?

00:19:09.867 --> 00:19:11.800
Aren't you going to be late?

00:19:11.800 --> 00:19:13.800
Huh? Why? What time is it?

00:19:13.800 --> 00:19:15.867
Oh, you're right!
Okay, wait.

00:19:15.867 --> 00:19:17.633
You can have my breakfast.

00:19:17.633 --> 00:19:19.933
Eat well, brother.
I love you.

00:19:19.933 --> 00:19:21.433
See you later, okay?

00:19:24.033 --> 00:19:26.200
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

00:19:29.333 --> 00:19:30.867
The police have left, ma'am.

00:19:32.267 --> 00:19:34.033
They're done talking
to the kids.

00:19:36.433 --> 00:19:37.700
Alright, Roy.

00:19:38.633 --> 00:19:39.767
Thank you.

00:19:40.967 --> 00:19:44.933
If we need to leave,
just let me know

00:19:44.933 --> 00:19:46.733
so I can get the car ready.

00:19:54.333 --> 00:20:01.300
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

00:20:09.800 --> 00:20:11.767
[WOMAN]
We're sorry for your loss.

00:20:11.767 --> 00:20:12.933
[KIKO] Thank you.

00:20:15.433 --> 00:20:16.967
[KIKO EXHALES DEEPLY]

00:20:17.600 --> 00:20:20.267
- We're sorry for your loss.
- Thank you.

00:20:20.867 --> 00:20:21.967
[WOMAN] Oh, hi.

00:20:21.967 --> 00:20:23.433
You're here.

00:20:23.433 --> 00:20:27.267
[GUESTS CHATTERING]

00:20:32.767 --> 00:20:35.700
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

00:20:35.733 --> 00:20:37.867
I thought you weren't coming.

00:20:41.000 --> 00:20:42.300
Come on.

00:20:43.033 --> 00:20:44.933
Let's bury Papa.

00:20:46.333 --> 00:20:53.100
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:20:59.533 --> 00:21:00.433
Leon?

00:21:01.067 --> 00:21:02.067
Uh...

00:21:02.067 --> 00:21:04.367
Mind if I get some rest?

00:21:05.167 --> 00:21:06.333
Sure, if you're tired.

00:21:06.833 --> 00:21:08.133
Thank you, Leon.

00:21:08.833 --> 00:21:10.267
[HEELS CLACKING]

00:21:10.267 --> 00:21:14.467
[INDISTINCT CROWD CHATTER]

00:21:15.367 --> 00:21:17.600
My friends have been
waiting for me.

00:21:17.600 --> 00:21:18.833
Can I leave now?

00:21:19.367 --> 00:21:20.367
No!

00:21:20.367 --> 00:21:21.400
You stay.

00:21:21.833 --> 00:21:23.033
[OVERLAPPING CHATTER]

00:21:23.033 --> 00:21:29.667
- [GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]
- [HEAVY FOOTSTEPS]

00:21:37.700 --> 00:21:38.667
[FRIDA] Edward.

00:21:39.600 --> 00:21:40.767
Auntie.

00:21:40.767 --> 00:21:42.367
My sincerest condolences.

00:21:43.200 --> 00:21:44.200
- Thank you.
- Leon.

00:21:44.200 --> 00:21:45.233
Edward.

00:21:45.233 --> 00:21:47.400
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:21:47.400 --> 00:21:49.333
When did you get back
from Singapore?

00:21:49.633 --> 00:21:51.233
Just today, Auntie.

00:21:51.233 --> 00:21:52.367
Dad picked me up.

00:21:54.567 --> 00:21:56.267
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

00:21:56.267 --> 00:21:57.567
- Dad...
- Leon.

00:21:57.567 --> 00:21:59.133
- Uncle.
- Frida.

00:21:59.133 --> 00:22:00.033
[FRIDA SIGHS DEEPLY]

00:22:00.033 --> 00:22:02.200
You have our
sincerest condolences.

00:22:02.200 --> 00:22:04.567
We attended the burial earlier,
but we chose not to go near

00:22:04.567 --> 00:22:06.367
when you were having your
final moments with your dad.

00:22:06.867 --> 00:22:08.300
[LEON] I appreciate it, Uncle.

00:22:08.300 --> 00:22:15.200
[GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:22:36.500 --> 00:22:43.400
[MUSIC SWELLING]

00:22:50.467 --> 00:22:51.567
Papa...

00:22:52.533 --> 00:22:54.167
All of us are here.

00:22:54.167 --> 00:22:55.500
We're finally complete.

00:23:05.167 --> 00:23:11.833
[THRILLING MUSIC PLAYING]

00:23:24.333 --> 00:23:26.167
[MUSIC INTENSIFYING]

00:23:27.533 --> 00:23:32.067
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

00:23:32.067 --> 00:23:35.400
Gentlemen, I've prepared some
coffee and snacks for you.

00:23:35.400 --> 00:23:36.300
[PLATE THUDS]

00:23:36.300 --> 00:23:38.367
- I'll pass.
- Just coffee for me.

00:23:46.467 --> 00:23:47.467
Goodness.

00:23:47.467 --> 00:23:49.300
I still find it hard to believe

00:23:49.300 --> 00:23:51.233
that Papa and Uncle Fred
went after each other.

00:23:51.233 --> 00:23:52.567
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:23:52.567 --> 00:23:54.500
They were still with us
just the other day,

00:23:55.367 --> 00:23:57.067
having a nice conversation.

00:23:57.733 --> 00:23:59.500
It should've been
a memorable get-together

00:23:59.500 --> 00:24:00.667
between two families.

00:24:02.067 --> 00:24:04.367
We hadn't been with Papa
for a long time.

00:24:05.433 --> 00:24:06.467
Honestly,

00:24:07.100 --> 00:24:10.167
I can't say I really knew him.

00:24:10.167 --> 00:24:12.100
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

00:24:12.100 --> 00:24:13.200
Me too.

00:24:14.533 --> 00:24:17.100
And we don't even know
what transpired

00:24:17.100 --> 00:24:18.400
in their conversation.

00:24:19.667 --> 00:24:21.967
There's so much
we don't know about them.

00:24:23.667 --> 00:24:27.400
Personally, I'm choosing to
believe what the police said.

00:24:27.700 --> 00:24:34.667
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

00:24:41.467 --> 00:24:42.433
I'm here.

00:24:43.200 --> 00:24:44.100
Ma?

00:24:44.200 --> 00:24:48.100
This hotel holds
many cherished memories.

00:24:48.100 --> 00:24:50.133
Please don't put Hotel 88
up for sale.

00:24:50.133 --> 00:24:51.533
If we lose this hotel,

00:24:51.533 --> 00:24:53.300
we'll never know what it is.

00:24:53.300 --> 00:24:55.433
If we were to make
this hotel operational,

00:24:55.433 --> 00:24:57.100
the three of us could
earn some money.

00:24:57.100 --> 00:24:58.500
We're expected to divide this?

00:25:01.600 --> 00:25:03.133
We have guests.

00:25:03.167 --> 00:25:06.133
Or should I say... co-owners?

00:25:06.133 --> 00:25:07.167
We want to buy your share.

00:25:07.167 --> 00:25:09.467
You can shove your money
down your throat!